## What is TOON?

TOON (Token-Oriented Object Notation) is a compact, human-readable encoding of the JSON data model that minimizes tokens for LLM input. It achieves ~40% fewer tokens compared to standard JSON/markdown tables while maintaining deterministic, lossless round-trips.

**Attribution:** TOON format was created by the toon-format project.
**Repository:** https://github.com/toon-format/toon

---

## Why Use TOON?

```toon
benefits[4]{benefit,description}:
 Token Efficiency,~40% fewer tokens vs markdown tables
 Explicit Schema,[N]{fields} headers improve LLM parsing
 Human Readable,CSV-like compact rows maintain readability
 Lossless,Deterministic round-trips to/from JSON
```

---

## Syntax Rules

### Array Header Format

```
name[count]{field1,field2,field3}:
```

- `name` - Identifier for the data
- `[count]` - Number of rows
- `{fields}` - Comma-separated field names
- `:` - Separator before data rows

### Data Rows

```
 value1,value2,value3
```

- Single space prefix for each row
- Comma-separated values matching header fields
- Use `/` for multiple values within a field (instead of `,`)

