## When to Use TOON

### Best For

- Uniform arrays of objects (tables with consistent columns)
- Configuration data with repeated structure
- Reference data that AI reads frequently
- Any tabular data in rules/documentation

### Less Suitable For

- Deeply nested structures
- Non-uniform data (varying fields per row)
- Code examples (keep as-is)
- Human-readable output templates

---

## Conversion Guidelines

### DO Convert

- Agent detection tables
- Workflow phase tables
- Scoring/threshold tables
- Configuration mappings
- Reference data tables

### DO NOT Convert

- Code examples in documentation
- Template output examples (meant for humans)
- Single-row data (no benefit)
- Complex nested structures

